Ri did not mention plans for a summit between Kim and Trump any more, as the US leader highlighted at the UN earlier this week.
The minister instead highlighted three meetings between Kim and South Korean leader Moon Jae-in within the past five months, adding: "If nuclear disarmament were to be negotiated with South Korea and not the United States, the negotiations would not be so stalemate."
